# üìò Library Management System ‚Äì Maven + JUnit

---

## 1Ô∏è‚É£ pom.xml

```xml
<project xmlns="http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0"
         xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
         xsi:schemaLocation="http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0
         http://maven.apache.org/xsd/maven-4.0.0.xsd">

    <modelVersion>4.0.0</modelVersion>

    <groupId>com.example</groupId>
    <artifactId>LIBRARY_MANAGEMENT_MAVEN</artifactId>
    <version>1.0-SNAPSHOT</version>

    <name>Library Management Application</name>

    <properties>
        <maven.compiler.source>17</maven.compiler.source>
        <maven.compiler.target>17</maven.compiler.target>
        <project.build.sourceEncoding>UTF-8</project.build.sourceEncoding>
    </properties>

    <dependencies>

        <dependency>
            <groupId>org.junit.jupiter</groupId>
            <artifactId>junit-jupiter</artifactId>
            <version>5.10.0</version>
            <scope>test</scope>
        </dependency>

    </dependencies>

    <build>
        <plugins>

            <plugin>
                <groupId>org.apache.maven.plugins</groupId>
                <artifactId>maven-compiler-plugin</artifactId>
                <version>3.11.0</version>
            </plugin>

            <plugin>
                <groupId>org.apache.maven.plugins</groupId>
                <artifactId>maven-surefire-plugin</artifactId>
                <version>3.1.2</version>
            </plugin>

        </plugins>
    </build>

</project>
```

---

## 2Ô∏è‚É£ Create `Library.java`

```java
package com.example;

public class Library {

    private int totalBooks;

    public Library(int totalBooks) {
        this.totalBooks = totalBooks;
    }

    public int getTotalBooks() {
        return totalBooks;
    }

    public boolean issueBook(int numberOfBooks) {
        if (numberOfBooks <= totalBooks && numberOfBooks > 0) {
            totalBooks -= numberOfBooks;
            return true;
        }
        return false;
    }

    public void returnBook(int numberOfBooks) {
        if (numberOfBooks > 0) {
            totalBooks += numberOfBooks;
        }
    }

    public boolean isBookAvailable() {
        return totalBooks > 0;
    }
}
```

---

## 3Ô∏è‚É£ Create `LibraryTest.java` for JUnit Testing

```java
package com.example;

import org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;
import static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.*;

class LibraryTest {

    @Test
    void testInitialBooks() {
        Library library = new Library(10);
        assertEquals(10, library.getTotalBooks());
    }

    @Test
    void testIssueBookSuccess() {
        Library library = new Library(10);
        boolean result = library.issueBook(3);
        assertTrue(result);
        assertEquals(7, library.getTotalBooks());
    }

    @Test
    void testIssueBookFailure() {
        Library library = new Library(5);
        boolean result = library.issueBook(6);
        assertFalse(result);
        assertEquals(5, library.getTotalBooks());
    }

    @Test
    void testReturnBook() {
        Library library = new Library(5);
        library.returnBook(2);
        assertEquals(7, library.getTotalBooks());
    }

    @Test
    void testBookAvailability() {
        Library library = new Library(1);
        assertTrue(library.isBookAvailable());

        library.issueBook(1);
        assertFalse(library.isBookAvailable());
    }
}
```

---

# ‚úÖ What This Program Does

* Maintains total number of books
* Issues books (reduces count)
* Returns books (increases count)
* Checks availability
* Fully tested using JUnit 5

